'''"Say You Will"''' is a song by [[United Kingdom|British]]-[[United States|American]] [[rock music|rock]] [[music band|band]] [[Foreigner (band)|Foreigner]]. It was the first single   released from the album ''[[Inside Information]]'' (1987), and was co-written by [[Lou Gramm]] and [[Mick Jones (Foreigner)|Mick Jones]]  (See [[1987 in music]]). It reached the #6 position on the [[Billboard Hot 100]] chart, and was #1 on the [[Mainstream Rock Tracks]] chart in the United States for a total of 4 weeks, starting on December 19, 1987.<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/retrieve_chart_history.do?model.vnuArtistId=4650&model.vnuAlbumId=168448 Billboard - Foreigner Chart History] (Retrieved on [[November 3]], [[2008]])</ref>

"Say You Will" was one of Foreigner's last two Top 10 chart hits in the United States, followed by the 1988 release of the single "[[I Don't Want to Live Without You]]" (which reached #5 on the Hot 100 chart). The single had less commercial success in other countries. The video clip for this song, directed by [[David Fincher]], peaked at #2 in [[MTV]]'s Top Ten chart in December 1987.<ref>[http://www.mtv.com MTV Charts] (Retrieved on [[November 3]], [[2008]])</ref>

